# Testing Conventions

- Framework: Jest + Supertest for API/integration tests.
- One test file per resource (e.g. `ticket.test.js`, `comment.test.js`).
- Every state-machine transition in `state-machine.mdc` gets its own test case — valid transitions assert success, invalid ones assert rejection with the right status code.
- Test names describe behavior, not implementation, e.g. "rejects transition from Closed to any status", not "test3".
- Reset/seed the database between test runs so tests are order-independent.
- Don't mock the database for integration tests — use a real (test) Postgres file so persistence is actually exercised.
- A test that always passes regardless of the code is worse than no test — assert on actual response bodies and status codes.
